"Sonechkin D.M., Datsenko N.M., Ivashchenko N.N.","Estimation of the global warming trend by wavelet analysis",1997,"Izvestiya - Atmospheric and Ocean Physics","33","2",,"167","176",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0031473493&partnerID=40&md5=d691df139918300cebcf90bccb4b4aee","Hydrometeorological Res. Ctr. R., Bol'shoi Predtechenskii per. 9-13, Moscow, 123242, Russian Federation","Sonechkin, D.M., Hydrometeorological Res. Ctr. R., Bol'shoi Predtechenskii per. 9-13, Moscow, 123242, Russian Federation; Datsenko, N.M., Hydrometeorological Res. Ctr. R., Bol'shoi Predtechenskii per. 9-13, Moscow, 123242, Russian Federation; Ivashchenko, N.N., Hydrometeorological Res. Ctr. R., Bol'shoi Predtechenskii per. 9-13, Moscow, 123242, Russian Federation","The self-similar (scaling) structure of temporal oscillations of the annual mean global surface air temperature during 1854-1990 is studied by wavelet analysis. These oscillations are divided into a statistically stationary part with a typical variation of about 0.5°C/10 years and a trend of global warming with an increment of 0.58-0.69°C/100 years. The trend has been found since 1900. Separate extrapolations of the oscillatory part and the trend at the end of the 20th century indicate that further growth of the global surface air temperature will possibly be checked.",,"air temperature; climate change; global warming; wavelet analysis",,,,,,"Sneyers, R., (1992) Report on the Informal Planning Meeting on Statistical Procedures for Climate Change Detection, pp. j76-j81. , Toronto, 25 June 1992, WMO, WCDMP-20; Budyko, M.I., (1972) Vliyanie Cheloveka Na Klimat (The Impact of the Man on the Climate), , Leningrad: Gidrometeoizdat; Budyko, M.I., The Effect of Solar Radiation Variations on the Climate of the Earth (1969) Tellus, 21 (5), pp. 611-619; Mandelbrot, B.B., Van Ness, J.W., Fractional Brownian Motions, Fractional Noises, and Applications (1968) SIAM Rev., 10 (4), pp. 422-437; Flandrin, P., On the Spectrum of Fractional Brownian Motion (1989) IEEE Trans. Inf. Theory, 35 (1), pp. 197-199; Lovejoy, S., Schertzer, D., Scale Invariance in Climatological Temperatures and the Spectral Plateau (1986) Ann. Geophys. B, 4 (4), pp. 401-410; Combes, J.M., Grossmann, A., Tchamitchian, Ph., (1989) Wavelets, , Berlin: Springer; Chui, C.K., (1992) An Introduction to Wavelets, , Boston: Academic; Datsenko, N.M., Sonechkin, D.M., Wavelet Analysis of Time Series and Atmospheric Dynamics (1993) Izv. Vyssh. Uchebn. Zaved., Prikl. Nelineinaya Din., 1 (1-2), pp. 9-14; Frik, P.G., Wavelet Analysis and Hierarchical Models of Turbulence (1992) Preprint of Inst. of Continuum Mechanics, Ural Division, Russ. Acad. Sci., , Perm'; Astaf'eva, N.M., Pokrovskaya, I.V., Sharkov, E.A., Hierarchical Structure of the Global Tropical Cyclogenesis (1994) Issled. Zemli Iz Kosmosa, (2), pp. 14-23; Boden, T.A., Sepanski, R.J., Stoss, F.W., (1991) Trends'91 - Highlights. A Compendium of Data on Global Change, , Carbon Dioxide Information Analysis Center, Oak Ridge National Laboratory, Oak Ridge, Tennessee, USA; Argoul, F., Wavelet Analysis of Turbulence Reveals the Multifractal Nature of the Richardson Cascade (1989) Nature, 338, pp. 51-53; Jones, P.D., Wigley, T.M., Kelly, P.M., Variations in Surface Air Temperature. Part 1: Northern Hemisphere, 1881-1980 (1982) Mon. Weather Rev., 110 (1), pp. 59-70; Lindzen, R.S., Some Coolness Concerning Global Warming (1990) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 71 (3), pp. 288-299; Ghil, M., Vautard, R., Interdecadal Oscillations and the Warming Trend in Global Temperature Time Series (1991) Nature, 350, pp. 324-327; Grossmann, A., Detection of Abrupt Changes in Sound Signals with the Help of Wavelet Transforms (1987) Inverse Problems, pp. 289-306. , New York: Academic; Mallat, S., Zhong, S., Characterization of Signals from Multiscale Edges (1992) IEEE Trans. Pattern Anal. Mach. Intell., 14 (7), pp. 710-732; Goossens, Ch., Berger, A., Annual and Seasonal Climatic Variations over the